introduction_key3: Aapne `string`, `integer`, `float` aur `booleans` data types ke baarein mei padha hoga. Yeh `primitive data types` kehlaye jaate hai. `Primitive` ka yaha matlab hai `simple` data types, jinka use kar kar hum aur `complex` data types bana sakte hai.
introduction_key4: `List` aisa hi ek `complex` data type hai.
introduction_key6: Aap Zindagi mei 10 kya cheezein karna chahte ho, uski list banao.
introduction_key7: Ab iss ko ek `python` mei `variables` mei store karne ki koshish karo
introduction_key8: Aise aap ko bahut baari, `information` ek `list`  ki form mei milegi. Jaise
introduction_key9: Groceries ki list jo aapko khareedni hai
introduction_key10: Courses ki list jo aapko NavGurukul mei karne
introduction_key11: Questions ki list jo aapko kisi course mei karne hai
introduction_key12: Kuch acchi habits ki list jo aap ko acche se program karne mei help kar sakti
introduction_key13: Kuch companies ki list jaha aap job karna chahte hai
introduction_key14: Aapke campus mei students ki list
introduction_key17: Hum aage dekhenge ki `lists` kitna useful `data type` ya `data structure` hai.
